                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/95.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Vice
                        Consul <persName type="to">Davis</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 158.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 8, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch No.
                    508, of September 10, 1914, concerning a special tax of ten thousand pesos
                    imposed against the National Cracker Company, Limited, by General Alvaro
                    Obregon, of the Constitutionalist Army, on July 29, 1914.</p>
                <p>The Department approves your action in making representations against the forced
                    loan imposed upon the National Cracker Company, and considers that you would be
                    justified in making such representations on behalf of any company concerning
                    which it is clearly proven that a majority of the stock is held by American
                    citizens. In any doubtful cases, however, the matter should first be submitted
                    to the Department for instructions. I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
